creator: Max Arthur Macauliffe
description:
LibriVox recording of The Sikh Religion: Its Gurus, Sacred Writings and Authors, Volume 2 by Max Arthur Macauliffe.
Read in English by Chiquito Crasto

This is one of the first (and still one of the few) comprehensive books about the Sikh religion in the English language. MacAuliffe had extensive access to manuscripts of the Sikh sacred writings (the Granth), as well as support from Sikh scholars and leaders of the time. This volume covers Guru Angad, Guru Amar Das and Guru Ram Das. This is volume two of six. - Summary from SacredTexts.com

For further information, including links to online text, reader information, RSS feeds, CD cover or other formats (if available), please go to the LibriVox catalog page for this recording.

For more free audio books or to become a volunteer reader, visit LibriVox.org.
